headlines.description: — Kyle Lowry scored 12 of his 25 points after regulation and the Miami Heat entered the All-Star break tied for the Eastern Conference lead, rallying to beat the Charlotte Hornets 111-107 in double overtime Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Lowry, Heat battle back to beat Hornets 111-107 in 2OT

headlines.description: — Rui Hachimura scored 20 points, Corey Kispert added 16 and the Washington Wizards beat the Brooklyn Nets 117-103 on Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Hachimura, Kispert lead Wizards past Nets, 117-103

events.name: Dallas Mavericks at New Orleans Pelicans

headlines.description: — As Luka Doncic finished fielding questions about his latest highlight-filled, high-scoring performance, a Dallas staff member told him to enjoy the All-Star break.
headlines.shortLinkText: Luka Doncic scores 49 points, Mavs beat Pelicans 125-118

headlines.description: — With the regular season already two-thirds of the way over, the Philadelphia 76ers wanted to avoid entering the All-Star break on a losing streak.
headlines.shortLinkText: Embiid has huge game to help 76ers outlast Bucks, 123-120

headlines.description: — Marcus Morris Sr. scored 27 points and Luke Kennard added 25 as the Los Angeles Clippers sped to a 17-point lead in the first half and beat the Houston Rockets 142-111 Thursday night in the final game before the NBA’s All-Star break.
headlines.shortLinkText: Clippers race to early lead, cruise past Rockets 142-111
